import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    zip_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    ax = zip_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 7), color='c')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("States")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Zip Codes")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(["Number of Zip Codes"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['latitude'], data['longitude'])
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Longitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by county and count the number of zip codes
    zip_count = data.groupby('county')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    
    # Sort the data by the number of zip codes in descending order
    zip_count = zip_count.sort_values('zip_code', ascending=False)
    
    # Create a bar chart
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 10))
    plt.bar(zip_count['county'][:10], zip_count['zip_code'][:10])
    plt.xlabel('County')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different counties?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by city and count the number of zip codes
    city_zip_counts = data.groupby('city')['zip_code'].count().sort_values(ascending=False)

    # Create a bar chart
    ax = city_zip_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='blue', alpha=0.5)

    # Set the title and labels
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different cities?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('City')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')

    # Rotate x-axis labels for better readability
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    # Add a legend
    ax.legend(['Number of Zip Codes'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
